# Solution Strategy (arc42 §4)

Applies to `3-arch/solution-strategy.md`. Source of truth for `NFR-##` and `ADR-##`.

**Templates:** [templates.md — solution-strategy](../consultation/templates.md#solution-strategymd) · **Traceability:** [06-traceability.mdc](06-traceability.mdc)

## Gate — required before downstream updates

Do **not** create or materially update `building-blocks.md`, `runtime-views.md`, `db-and-dfd.md`, or assign feature **Blocks** / **Runtime flow** participants until **solution strategy is ready** ([Ready checklist](#ready-checklist)).

Stop and report using [Cancel response](#cancel-response) if the gate fails.

## Prerequisites

Create or regenerate only when:

1. Interview completed and user confirmed ([01-interview.mdc](01-interview.mdc))
2. `stakeholders-and-goals.md` has ≥1 `GOL-##` and **Constraints** / **Assumptions** reviewed
3. `features-list.md` exists; every **Must** `F##` has `F##_*.md` with **Overview** and ≥1 UR (or interview confirms NFR-only scope)

If scope or Must features are incomplete, finish or stub per [02-features-list.mdc](02-features-list.mdc); record gaps in `open-questions.md` (`Q-S##` / `Q-F##-##`), not in solution-strategy.

## Inputs (read order)

| Order | Source | Use |
|-------|--------|-----|
| 1 | `stakeholders-and-goals.md` — **Constraints**, **Assumptions**, **Non-Goals** | Context, NFRs, risks |
| 2 | `business-scenarios.md` — **Context and Boundary**, external actors | Context, integration ADRs |
| 3 | `features-list.md` + all `F##_*.md` | NFR needs, FR non-functional types, feature links |
| 4 | Existing `solution-strategy.md` | Preserve accepted ADRs; extend only |

Do not invent NFRs, ADRs, or stack choices unsupported by scope, features, or confirmed interview answers.

## Derivation procedure

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 Context | Problem space, forces, boundary — from scope + scenarios |
| 2 NFRs | Extract non-functional needs from goals, constraints, Must features; IDs `NFR-01`…; **Features** column lists each `F##` |
| 3 ADRs | Record structural/tech choices implied by constraints or features; IDs `ADR-01`…; **Affects** lists `F##`; add `BB-##` when blocks exist |
| 4 Stack | Technology Stack table — every row cites an ADR |
| 5 Quality goals | Prioritize top NFRs (1–5 rows) |
| 6 Risks | From assumptions, constraints, ADR consequences |
| 7 Validate | [Ready checklist](#ready-checklist) |
| 8 Propagate | Feature **Overview** **Trace** NFR links; `traceability.md`; remove resolved `Q-A##` from `open-questions.md` |

**ADR status:** `Proposed` while interviewing; set `Accepted` before calling strategy ready.

## Ready checklist

Solution strategy is **ready** when all pass:

- [ ] All template sections present and filled (not placeholder-only)
- [ ] **No open rows** in `open-questions.md` **Architecture** section (`Q-A##`)
- [ ] Every **Must** `F##` appears in ≥1 NFR **Features** or ADR **Affects**, or Overview **Trace** cites `NFR-##`
- [ ] Every `NFR-##` **Features** and ADR **Affects** link resolves
- [ ] Technology Stack rows reference existing ADRs
- [ ] Quality Goals reference existing NFRs
- [ ] ADRs that constrain building-blocks or stack choices are **Accepted** (not `Proposed`)
- [ ] User confirmed strategy in interview summary

## When to update

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| Scope constraints / assumptions | Context, NFRs, risks |
| New or changed Must feature | NFR **Features**; ADR **Affects**; re-run gate before BB |
| Tech or quality decision | ADR + Stack; propagate to BB if decomposition changes |
| ADR accepted / superseded | Status, consequences; building-blocks if **Affects** changes |
| Architecture question answered | Record in target section; **remove** `Q-A##` row |

After material strategy change, re-validate downstream (`building-blocks.md`, `runtime-views.md`, `db-and-dfd.md`) in the same pass or flag stale refs in interview summary.

## Cancel response

```
Cancelled: <target doc or task>
Blocker: solution-strategy
Reason: <one sentence — e.g. open Q-A02; ADR-03 still Proposed>
Resolve: <complete ready checklist; see 04-solution-strategy.mdc>
```
